description.html: The box-shadow property adds one or more shadows to an element, allowing for effects like drop shadows. You can customize the shadow's offset, blur radius, spread, and color to achieve various visual effects. If you're not comfortable writing the syntax manually, there are plenty of CSS generators that can help you create the perfect box-shadow values. Check out these tools: CSS Box Shadow Generator and CSSmatic Box Shadow Generator.
description.text: The box-shadow property allows you to attach one or more shadows to an element. It offers customization of shadow offsets, blur radius, spread, and color to create various visual effects. For those less familiar with the syntax, numerous CSS generators can help you easily generate this code. Examples include CSS Box Shadow Generator (https://cssgenerator.pl/en/box-shadow-generator/) and CSSmatic Box Shadow Generator (https://www.cssmatic.com/box-shadow).
